paper_abstract: In this paper we report the following computational results on partial spread functions in eight variables: (i) the numbers of equivalence classes of partial spread functions (in eight variables) of all possible orders; (ii) the total number of partial spread bent functions in eight variables; (iii) the distribution of the cardinalities of stabilizers (in GL(8, F(2))) of partial spread bent functions in eight variables. The computational method is also described.
paper_title: Counting Partial Spread Functions in Eight Variables
